<TEXT>
walter dunfey cofounder and former director of 
dunfey hotels died sunday at massachusetts general hospital he was 
57 
dunfey a rye nh resident died about 4 pm from 
complications related to an aneurysm he suffered aug 3 
dunfey helped build dunfey hotels business into an international 
corporation which was later sold and is now known as omni hotels 
in december 1987 he and four of his brothers formed the dunfey 
brothers capital group a venture capital and investment company 
dunfey also was involved heavily in democratic politics both at 
the state and national levels he was a member of the democratic 
national committees business council as well as its convention 
site selection committee 
in 1960 thensen john kennedy began his presidential campaign 
from dunfeys office in the carpenter hotel in manchester nh 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
august a luebs a former university of 
nebraska professor who was a pioneer in air conditioning research 
died friday he was 100 
born in wood river on feb 28 1889 luebs joined the 
universitys faculty in 1918 he retired in 1958 after a 40year 
teaching career in the mechanical engineering department 
as a result of his research in the 1930s luebs perfected a 
method of measuring fuel requirements in air conditioning called a 
degreeday which still is used today he also established 
ratings for both oil and gasheating equipment 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bishop john j cassata the first bishop 
of the catholic diocese of fort worth died friday at age 80 
cassata died in a houston hospital from complications after heart 
surgery 
he had led the 28county diocese from its formation in 1969 until 
his retirement in 1980 
</TEXT>
